 {"id":"asupersync-or5","title":"[Sync] Implement Two-Phase Semaphore with Permits","description":"# Two-Phase Semaphore

## Overview
Counting semaphore with two-phase permit acquisition for cancel-safety.

## Core Type

```rust
pub struct Semaphore {
    /// Available permits
    permits: AtomicUsize,
    /// Waiter queue
    waiters: WaiterQueue,
    /// Closed flag
    closed: AtomicBool,
}

impl Semaphore {
    /// Create with n permits
    pub const fn new(permits: usize) -> Self {
        Self {
            permits: AtomicUsize::new(permits),
            waiters: WaiterQueue::new(),
            closed: AtomicBool::new(false),
        }
    }

    /// Available permits
    pub fn available_permits(&self) -> usize {
        self.permits.load(Ordering::Acquire)
    }

    /// Acquire permit (two-phase)
    pub async fn acquire(&self) -> Result<SemaphorePermit<'_>, SemaphoreError> {
        self.acquire_many(1).await.map(|p| SemaphorePermit { inner: p })
    }

    /// Acquire multiple permits
    pub async fn acquire_many(&self, n: usize) -> Result<SemaphorePermitMany<'_>, SemaphoreError>;

    /// Try to acquire immediately
    pub fn try_acquire(&self) -> Option<SemaphorePermit<'_>>;

    /// Try to acquire many immediately
    pub fn try_acquire_many(&self, n: usize) -> Option<SemaphorePermitMany<'_>>;

    /// Add permits (can exceed initial count)
    pub fn add_permits(&self, n: usize);

    /// Close semaphore (wake all waiters with error)
    pub fn close(&self);

    /// Check if closed
    pub fn is_closed(&self) -> bool {
        self.closed.load(Ordering::Acquire)
    }
}
```

## Permits (Obligations)

```rust
/// Single permit (obligation to release)
pub struct SemaphorePermit<'a> {
    inner: SemaphorePermitMany<'a>,
}

impl SemaphorePermit<'_> {
    /// Forget permit (don't return to semaphore)
    pub fn forget(self) {
        self.inner.forget()
    }
}

impl Drop for SemaphorePermit<'_> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        // Permit released - returns to semaphore
        self.inner.semaphore.add_permits(1);
    }
}

/// Multiple permits
pub struct SemaphorePermitMany<'a> {
    semaphore: &'a Semaphore,
    count: usize,
    forgotten: bool,
}

impl SemaphorePermitMany<'_> {
    pub fn forget(mut self) {
        self.forgotten = true;
        std::mem::forget(self);
    }
}

impl Drop for SemaphorePermitMany<'_> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        if \!self.forgotten {
            self.semaphore.add_permits(self.count);
        }
    }
}
```

## Owned Permits

```rust
pub struct OwnedSemaphorePermit {
    semaphore: Arc<Semaphore>,
}

impl Semaphore {
    pub async fn acquire_owned(self: Arc<Self>) -> Result<OwnedSemaphorePermit, SemaphoreError> {
        self.acquire().await?;
        Ok(OwnedSemaphorePermit { semaphore: self })
    }
}

impl Drop for OwnedSemaphorePermit {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        self.semaphore.add_permits(1);
    }
}
```

## Error Type

```rust
pub enum SemaphoreError {
    /// Semaphore was closed
    Closed,
    /// Acquisition was cancelled
    Cancelled,
}
```

## Two-Phase Pattern

The permit is the "reservation" phase:
1. acquire() -> SemaphorePermit (reserved)
2. Use the protected resource
3. Drop permit (released) OR forget (consumed)

```rust
// Example: connection pool
let permit = pool.acquire().await?;
let conn = pool.get_connection(&permit);
// ... use connection ...
// permit dropped, connection returned to pool
```

## Cancel-Safety
- acquire(): cancel = no permit acquired
- Permit Drop always returns to semaphore (unless forgotten)
- close() wakes all waiters with error

## Testing
- Basic acquire/release
- Exhaustion and waiting
- try_acquire when empty
- add_permits beyond initial
- close() behavior
- forget() behavior
- Cancel during acquire

